---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Docs">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner docs">
      <p class="eyebrow">Docs</p>
      <h1>Watchtower reference</h1>
      <p class="lead">A concise guide to using Heimdall for tracking cryptocurrency growth and network health.</p>
      <article class="card">
        <h2>Getting started</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Connect to your preferred blockchain nodes or use Heimdall's default node endpoints.</li>
          <li>Select the networks you want to track: Bitcoin, Ethereum, or emerging chains.</li>
          <li>Configure growth alerts for price velocity, volume spikes, or network health changes.</li>
          <li>Export historical data for research and long-term trend analysis.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h2>Data sources</h2>
        <pre><code>Bitcoin node: bitcoind RPC or public endpoint
Ethereum node: geth / erigon / infura (fallback)
Validator data: Beacon chain API
Price feeds: Aggregated exchange data (no single source)</code></pre>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .docs {
    display: grid;
    gap: 24px;
  }

  ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 22px;
    color: #354052;
  }

  pre {
    overflow: auto;
    margin: 0;
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: #111827;
    color: #fff;
    padding: 18px;
  }
</style>
